                      <locus target="#ii v(erso) #iiir(ecto) #iiiv(erso) #ivr(ecto)"/> <title type="complete" ref="LIT1398Fethat"/> from the Missal
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a03">
                      <desc type="RecordTransaction">
                      <locus target="#200v #202v"/> Note of transaction of various items: land, dress, herbs, etc
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e01">
                      <desc>
                      Psalm 118 contains the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e02">
                      <desc>
                      Numbered quires: quires 2, 3, 4, 5, 7 on the verso of the last folio
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e03">
                      <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#10r #17r #72r #77v"/>, etc.);
                      and in the upper margin with a symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#39v"/>, line 17; <locus target="#46v"/>, line 17), and in another case where the symbol (+) is used (<locus target="#75r"/>, line 3);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#19v #41v #122v"/>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e04">
                      <desc>
                      The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate
                      aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line
                      of text above or below the end of the line (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto
                      the next line (e.g., <locus target="#3v #5rv #6r"/>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>

                    </list>
                  </additions>
